            <div type="typology">
               <p>Dialect group: Maghreb, Tunisia</p>
               <p>Urban sedentary dialect, Sāḥil group</p>
            </div>
            <div type="general">
               <p>Sousse is an important coastal city in the west of Tunisia which
                  has been a regional trade centre for many centuries. Starting in
                  the 1960s Sousse has developed into one of the country’s main
                  Tourism destinations. This caused immense increase in population,
                  especially migration from rural areas all over Tunisia, which has
                  significantly influenced the original dialect.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="researchHistory">
               <p>A detailed study on the dialect spoken within
                  the medina is <rs type="bibl" ref="zotid:VNHH49Z2">Talmoudi (1980)</rs>, a
                  collection of texts can be found in <rs type="bibl" ref="zotid:NP7ZI6PP">Talmoudi (1981)</rs>. An
                  analysis of verbs of Romance origin in Tunisian dialects,
                  including data from Sousse, is given in <rs type="bibl" ref="zotid:5WDMXBJ9">Talmoudi (1986)</rs>.
                  <rs type="bibl" ref="zotid:G5R6TQS8">Saada (1956)</rs> is a study
                  about the dialect of the Jews of Sousse.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography">
               <p>To view publications on this variety click <rs type="bibl" ref="bibl:geo:Sousse">here</rs>.</p>
